	<div class="wrapper">
		<h1>Tooltippy</h1>
		
		<p>Out on the net are some wonderful CSS-only tooltip solutions that convert attributes such as titles, names or data to the tooltip text. However, for a project I needed to include HTML in the tooltip.</p>
		
		<p>As I soon found out, a centred tooltip is nice in design, but won't wash in real life, with right and left-aligned text that can sit close to the top or bottom of a page and that also needs to be responsive.</p>
		
		<p>So I've made this tooltip flexible, changing its position by a few added clas
